pageContext.claim: “80% of the RIOTERS in Minneapolis last night were from OUT OF STATE. They are harming businesses (especially African American small businesses), homes, and the community of good, hardworking Minneapolis residents who want peace, equality, and to provide for their families.”
pageContext.analysis: This was a false report, picked up not only by Trump but also figures like House Speaker Nancy Pelosi. State officials quickly backed off the claim once arrest records showed howed that 86% of those arrested listed Minnesota as their address.
